        <item>
            <title>1.7.1 beta</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:39:52 +0200</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[<div style="font-family:'Arial'">
  <p>1.7.1</p>
    <div>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <b>Audio Compression</b><br/>
                A dynamic compressor can now be enabled in Settings &gt; General to reduce the volume difference
                between loud and quiet passages during playback.<br/><br/>

                <b>How to enable:</b> Go to Settings &gt; General and check "Enable Compression". Then reload the
                currently loaded song for the change to take effect.<br/><br/>

                <b>Parameters:</b>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Threshold (dB):</b> The volume level above which compression kicks in.
                        A lower value (e.g. -24 dB) means more of the audio gets compressed.
                        Default: -18 dB.</li>
                    <li><b>Head Room (dB):</b> Controls how gently the compression is applied.
                        A higher value results in softer, more gradual compression.
                        Default: 5 dB.</li>
                    <li><b>Master Gain (dB):</b> Makeup gain to restore overall volume after compression
                        has reduced the louder parts. Increase this if the song sounds too quiet after
                        compression. Default: 0 dB.</li>
                </ul><br/>

                Click the info button (?) next to the compression settings for a quick reference of
                these parameters.<br/>
                <br/>
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Improved Audio Normalization for stereo files</b><br/>
                The normalization algorithm now correctly analyzes both channels of stereo files and uses
                the peak of the louder channel to calculate the gain adjustment, preventing clipping on
                either side.<br/>
                <br/>
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Clock Window improvements</b><br/>
                The title bar and traffic light buttons have been removed for a cleaner look.
                Additionally, the clock window can now become fully transparent when it is not
                being hovered with the mouse. Enable this in Settings &gt; General with the
                "Transparent when inactive" option. When you move the mouse over the clock window
                it returns to its normal appearance; move the mouse away and it fades back to
                transparent.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>]]></description>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>12.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <enclosure url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lunk22/ClogAmpSwiftSparkle/master/appcast/ClogAmpMac.app-1.7.1.zip" sparkle:version="1.7.1" sparkle:shortVersionString="1.7.1 beta" length="7666535" type="application/octet-stream" sparkle:edSignature="q5qo31wuNhT5phnaP9Uh86K5flogGhcnoQcX6HgTLpz/EeNmL8T+SgWJRq1aWxmjUmGIdZkThe2MjDD6qu19DA=="/>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>1.7.2 beta</title>
            <pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 16:42:15 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>12.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<div style="font-family:'Arial'">
                <p>1.7.2</p>
                    <div>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <b>Position Timeline</b><br/>
                                The seek slider in the player has been replaced by a visual timeline bar that shows all
                                dance positions at their exact time positions. A blue fill indicates playback progress,
                                a white playhead line marks the current position, and each named position appears as
                                a tick mark with its label below the bar. You can click or drag anywhere on the bar
                                to seek.<br/><br/>

                                The timeline is enabled by default. To switch back to the plain slider, go to
                                Settings &gt; General and uncheck "Show Timeline".<br/>
                                <br/>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Customizable Keyboard Shortcuts</b><br/>
                                All keyboard shortcuts can now be configured freely in Settings &gt; Shortcuts.
                                Shortcuts are organised into sections (File, Edit, Tools, Player, and Others) and
                                each action shows its current binding. Click a binding field and press the desired
                                key combination to reassign it; click it again while it is active to clear the
                                shortcut entirely.<br/><br/>

                                <b>Notable shortcuts in the "Others" section:</b>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><b>Jump to Position 1–10:</b> Press the corresponding digit key (1–0 on the
                                        number row) to jump directly to that position.</li>
                                    <li><b>Jump to Position 11–20:</b> Hold Shift while pressing the digit key.</li>
                                    <li><b>Play Position / Load Song:</b> Press Enter to play the selected position
                                        or load the selected song.</li>
                                </ul><br/>

                                Use the "Reset to Defaults" button at the bottom of the Shortcuts settings page to
                                restore all shortcuts to their factory values.<br/>
                                <br/>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>]]></description>
            <enclosure url="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lunk22/ClogAmpSwiftSparkle/master/appcast/ClogAmpMac.app-1.7.2.zip" sparkle:version="1.7.2" sparkle:shortVersionString="1.7.2 beta" length="7718593" type="application/octet-stream" sparkle:edSignature="HQeioeku6e4WeQ98t3REnnlzBZnhu4L3HD4XrjrrBQmSO0/szwPMCkA74kp7JgojNxrymONvMpy3ZuLm4tiZBQ=="/>
